        "title": "Having issue with the concept of extra semi-colon at the end of for loop in Java",
        "body": "<p>I was writing a code to insert an element at the end of the linked list. However without using the semi-colon at the end of for, I'm unable to get the list updated properly, what is the significance of this semi-colon and how is this affecting my code?<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public void insertAtEnd() throws IOException {\n        LinkedList node=new LinkedList();\n        System.out.println(\"Enter an element\");\n        int value=Integer.parseInt(br.readLine());\n        node.setData(value);\n        LinkedList p,q;\n        for(p=head; (q=p.getNext())!=null; p=q); \n            p.setNext(node);\n    }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
        "question_id": 36430012,
